Here are 100 programming questions related to strings, arrays, and similar concepts, grouped into 
different categories.

String Manipulation

Write a Java program to reverse a string without using the built-in reverse function.
Write a Java program to check if a string is a palindrome.
Write a Java program to count the number of vowels and consonants in a string.
Write a Java program to find the longest word in a given sentence.
Write a Java program to remove all white spaces from a string.
Write a Java program to capitalize the first letter of each word in a string.
Write a Java program to find all permutations of a given string.
Write a Java program to count occurrences of a substring in a string.
Write a Java program to replace all occurrences of a character in a string with another character.
Write a Java program to find the first repeating character in a string.
Write a Java program to find the longest substring without repeating characters.
Write a Java program to find the length of the shortest word in a sentence.
Write a Java program to check if a string is a valid binary string (contains only 0s and 1s).
Write a Java program to convert a string to title case (capitalize first letter of each word).
Write a Java program to reverse words in a string but keep the word order intact.
Write a Java program to find the longest common prefix in an array of strings.
Write a Java program to remove duplicate characters from a string.
Write a Java program to remove all punctuation from a string.
Write a Java program to check if a string contains only digits.
Write a Java program to count the number of words in a string.
Write a Java program to find the first non-repeating word in a sentence.
Write a Java program to reverse vowels in a string.
Write a Java program to replace spaces with hyphens in a string.
Write a Java program to find all unique characters in a string.
Write a Java program to check if two strings are rotations of each other.

